    "what_description": "Yushania hsuehiana is a species of bamboo in the family Poaceae. It has a woody stem up to 4 meters tall with internodes covered in a dense, dark brown to black sheath. The culms are cylindrical, glabrous, and have a diameter of 1-2 cm. The leaves are alternate, elliptic to lanceolate in shape, and 5-12 cm long with a petiole 1-3 cm long. The plant is endemic to Taiwan and typically grows in shaded, humid environments at elevations of 1,000-2,400 meters.",
