    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Yushania hsuehiana are yushania tea, yushania infusion, yushania tincture, decoction, and salve, which are derived from its rhizomes and stems. Yushania tea is made by infusing the rhizomes in hot water to yield a diuretic and anti-inflammatory liquid. Yushania infusion, a more concentrated liquid, is prepared by steeping the rhizomes in cold water to extract its bioactive compounds. Yushania tincture, a concentrated liquid extract, is prepared by soaking the rhizomes in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin to yield a medicinal liquid. Decoction and salve, derived from the rhizomes and stems, are used topically to treat wounds, skin irritations, and inflammation.",
