    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Yushania hsuehiana improperly include experiencing nausea, headaches, and dizziness due to its toxic compounds such as saponins and flavonoids, which can be released when the plant is mishandled or ingested in large quantities. These compounds can cause gastrointestinal problems, neurological issues, and allergic reactions. Ingestion of large amounts of Yushania hsuehiana can lead to allergic reactions such as skin irritation, respiratory problems, and anaphylaxis. The improper use of Yushania hsuehiana can also cause headaches and dizziness due to its neurotoxic properties. Overall, the misuse of Yushania hsuehiana can result in serious health complications and requires careful handling and administration.",
